<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,404,1440]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1307,1332]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Etymology.</emphasis>
From the Greek, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Williams &amp; Cambra &amp; Bartholomay &amp; Luz &amp; Quintero &amp; Pitts" authorityYear="2019" box="[540,632,1308,1331]" class="Insecta" family="Mutillidae" genus="Lomachaeta" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="eironeia">
<emphasis box="[540,632,1308,1331]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">eironeia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, irony, in reference to the fact that this specimen was recognized as a new species by KAW only a few months after 
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, K. A. &amp; Pitts, J. P." box="[672,922,1343,1368]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="227 - 243" refId="ref25741" refString="Williams, K. A. &amp; Pitts, J. P. (2009) Eight new species of Lomachaeta Mickel and the synonymy of Smicromutilla Mickel (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). Journal of Hymenoptera Research, 18 (2), 227 - 243." type="journal article" year="2009">Williams &amp; Pitts 2009</bibRefCitation>
was published.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="11" pageNumber="112" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="11.[151,1437,404,1440]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,1379,1404]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Remarks</emphasis>
. The genitalia of this species are truly bizarre (
<figureCitation box="[888,978,1379,1404]" captionStart="FIGURES 57–60" captionStartId="28.[151,264,1963,1986]" captionTargetBox="[186,1407,798,1949]" captionTargetId="figure@28.[186,1407,798,1949]" captionTargetPageId="28" captionText="FIGURES 57–60. Lomachaeta males; lateral habitus. 57) L. theresa; 58) L. snellingella; 59) L. eironeia, sp. nov.; 60) L. polemomechana. Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/2588794/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="112">Fig. 59</figureCitation>
), even for a genus with such variable parameres (
<bibRefCitation author="Williams, K. A. &amp; Pitts, J. P." box="[280,537,1415,1440]" pageId="11" pageNumber="112" pagination="227 - 243" refId="ref25741" refString="Williams, K. A. &amp; Pitts, J. P. (2009) Eight new species of Lomachaeta Mickel and the synonymy of Smicromutilla Mickel (Hymenoptera: Mutillidae). Journal of Hymenoptera Research, 18 (2), 227 - 243." type="journal article" year="2009">Williams &amp; Pitts 2009</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
